posts.name: Yongle Liu
posts.cooked: Hi guys we are preparing for the off season, and we would like to modify the fonts on our bumpers. I’m using Inventor to design the bumper styles and I’d like to learn what fonts do you recommend? Thanks!

posts.name: Ken Pontbriant
posts.cooked:
The font we use and the font I would recommend are not the same font.  For nearly our entire existence we’ve used a font named Boink LET:

image 585×740 35 KB

image 585×740 35 KB

image 585×740 35 KB

It’s easily visible and pretty much a defining trait for our team by now.

The font I would recommend is any non-serif font that meets the requirements of this past season, so unbroken characters with a stroke width of at least  1/2".

posts.name: Stewart Riley
posts.cooked:
We’ve been using the same font for a couple of years now, mostly because it’s actually one of the official branding fonts of FIRST, partially because of its utterly appropriate name, and partially because it’s just a great font for bumper numbers: Roboto . We use it in its bold, italic form to get a solid but kind of racy look to the numbers. Since we cut them on a vinyl cutter from insignia cloth, we can apply them as a group to the bumpers and get a perfect alignment and spacing. We think they look great and they’re certainly easy to read for refs and announcers. Here’s this season’s robot, Charles, with these numbers: Charles Ready to Start the First Match at States 1280×1252 266 KB

Charles Ready to Start the First Match at States 1280×1252 266 KB

Charles Ready to Start the First Match at States 1280×1252 266 KB

posts.name: Brennan Macaig
posts.cooked:
We use a modified custom font “Bauer” - it’s based on the logo for the hockey company. Our version is modified to be correctly kerned for our team name and numbers.

PXL_20230311_200329628 1920×2550 373 KB

PXL_20230311_200329628 1920×2550 373 KB

PXL_20230311_200329628 1920×2550 373 KB

We’ve used Hemi Head Bold-Italic as our main font since 2011 (I don’t believe we had any specific font in 2010). We use it as our main logo font on our shirts, promotional/media items, our bumpers, etc. We normally embroider on the letters, but this year we decided to use vinyl and heat press them on, (something that’d become very handy later in the season).
